shì yí gè fēi cháng fēi cháng fù yù de chéng shì
was an incredibly, incredibly wealthy city.

377
00:12:03,980 --> 00:12:06,100
它曾经一度呢人均收入超过了纽约
tā céng jīng yí dù ne rén jūn shōu rù chāo guò le niǔ yuē
At one point, its per capita income even surpassed New York's.

378
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,460
成为美国人均收入排名第一的城市
chéng wéi měi guó rén jūn shōu rù pái míng dì yī de chéng shì
making it the number one city in the U.S. for per capita income.

379
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:09,260
当然是因为汽车
dāng rán shì yīn wèi qì chē
And of course, it was all because of the cars.

380
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:12,260
大家都知道底特律有个外号叫做汽车上的城市
dà jiā dōu zhī dào dǐ tè lǜ yǒu gè wài hào jiào zuò qì chē shàng de chéng shì
As we all know, Detroit has a nickname: the Motor City.

381
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:14,660
美国人能80%的人都拥有汽车
měi guó rén néng 80% de rén dōu yōng yǒu qì chē
to the point where 80% of Americans owned a car.

382
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:17,180
而这些车在当年全部不能说全部
ér zhè xiē chē zài dāng nián quán bù bù néng shuō quán bù
And back in the day, you couldn't say all of these cars... well, not all of them...

383
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:19,540
大部分都是由美国的三大车企提供
