这个小姐姐他的时薪呢就是13块七毛三
zhè ge xiǎo jiě jiě tā de shí xīn ne jiù shì 13 kuài qī máo sān
So, for this young lady here, her hourly wage is thirteen seventy-three.

396
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:45,040
但是如果你在底特律呢
dàn shì rú guǒ nǐ zài dǐ tè lǜ ne
But what if you're in Detroit?

397
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:47,000
工厂里面做一份最普通的工作
gōng chǎng lǐ miàn zuò yī fèn zuì pǔ tōng de gōng zuò
and you're doing the most basic job in a factory,

398
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,139
你的最低时薪能够去到71小时
nǐ de zuì dī shí xīn néng gòu qù dào 71 xiǎo shí
your minimum hourly wage could be as high as 71 dollars.

399
00:12:50,139 --> 00:12:53,519
那这种情况呢就逼着当地的三大车企没有活路
nà zhè zhǒng qíng kuàng ne jiù bī zhe dāng dì de sān dà chē qǐ méi yǒu huó lù
And this situation, it basically forced the three major local car companies into a corner with no way out.

400
00:12:53,519 --> 00:12:55,199
因为他们平均每造出一辆车
yīn wèi tā men píng jūn měi zào chū yī liàng chē
Because on average, for every car they built,

401
00:12:55,199 --> 00:12:57,240
都比日企多了3000美金
